www.magpul.com/colorado

"Oh, but the bill might pass, buy my $50 mags."  No.  Even if the bill passes and is signed into law it won't be in effect until July 1.

Don't panic.  Don't get scammed.  Don't pay more than $15 for any mags.  Even USGI.  Magpul's deal will continue until July 1 if it passes or until the bill is killed in the legislature.  Either way, go to them first.

title: For Sale:  My letter, my actions do you agree?
location: spread the word, Colorado, United States
postcontent:
I have been following the press for stronger rules and regulations regarding gun laws, gun bans and bans on high cap magazines and I am disgusted with you all! I have worked Security and Executive Protection for most of my adult life and have been an upstanding member of any community I live in or pass through. I share my disgust with you today in hopes that someone may take notice of problems far more relevant than re-instating a list of bans that didn't work in the first place and perhaps look at your own broken house for the answers. "You say it is up to the Gun Owners to be responsible for their actions and the actions of others". BULLSHIT!

With that I want to tell you a short story,

    About a year ago I posted a small pistol and several other guns for sale on a site called armslist.com, a free site linking LAW ABIDING citizens and gun owners to each other across the nation with classified sales. To make short I am going to cut to it.

        I received a late night phone call from a young man in the Denver area requesting to buy the gun I had listed, I asked: What gun are you interested in buying? He says: I don't know, the small one, the cheapest one I can get... "ALARM". I felt something was wrong and I ended the phone call by referring that he go to a pawn shop for a cheap gun. About half hour later the sick feeling in my gut was enough that I decided to "Make a call" and report this, and this is where it gets sickening!

My first call at 10:44pm was to Denver Metro Police, where I was not able to file a report with anyone, in fact I was refused the time of day to report a "Child looking for a Gun", and told that it was "probably a prank call" and that they did not have the time or resources to investigate. "Note" A drive by and a knock takes maybe 10mins, they do this for accidental 911 calls! My Second Call was to the Sheriff's Department where I got a similar "We can not help you"... Frustrating, so I decide to take it up a notch and call the Denver Field Office for BATF&E, no answer, no nothing. On to WASHINGTON!!! When I connected with the woman at the BATF&E switchboard I was black-walled, she told me that it was not her job nor was it the job of the BATF&E "F is for Fire-Arms by the way", to look into this and I should contact my own local police department... Im thinking to myself at this point, "Who the hell are these people, Im trying to stop what I know in my gut is a disturbed young man from getting a hold of a gun... Columbine anyone?"

    It is now 2:00am and I am forcing my eyes and brain to remain open... I called the local Delta County Sheriff and finally someone who gives a shit! I will omit his/her name because it seems like people who work for this state who do good thing for the right reasons always end up getting hurt! The Deputy Immediately shared my concern that a young man who sounded very disturbed was searching for a small cheap handgun late at night....
